    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="760"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.5151/230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Greene</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-16T12:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 16, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Minister of Finance yesterday issued a decree suspending application of tax
                    on remittances by private persons, as well as a decree modifying approximately
                    as follows exchange regulations reported in <pb facs="0843" n="755"
                        xml:id="pg_755"/> my telegram number 118 of November 29. Exchange derived
                    from export of produce not regularly exported and foreign currency notes may be
                    freely negotiated, while exchange operations of private persons may be freely
                    effected. Exchange Control Committee attending only to applications from private
                    persons not exceeding 200 pesos per month. Authorized exchange dealers shall
                    declare all above transactions to Control Committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Greene</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
